The LITTLE OWLThe Greeks and Romans seem to
have had no name appro∣priated to this species; and probably they confounded
it with the Scops Owl, or Asio. This is the case in the modern
languages: both are termed Zuetta or Civetta in Italian;
Sechuza in Spanish; Mocho in Portuguese;
Kautzlein in German; and Szowa in Swe∣dish..

